{
  "id": 5113430155591680,
  "name": "Speculation rules: desktop \"eager\" eagerness improvements",
  "summary": "On desktop, \"eager\" eagerness speculation rules prefetches and prerenders now trigger when users hover on a link for a shorter time than the \"moderate\" mouse hover time.\r\n\r\nThe previous behavior, of starting prefetch/prerenders as soon as possible, was the same as \"immediate\" eagerness. This new behavior is more useful as it better reflects the author's intent to be more eager than the \"moderate\" and less eager than \"immediate\".\r\n\r\nMore detail on this and other upcoming improvements to speculation rules eagerness are available at https://docs.google.com/document/d/1YPbtUPfZIDElzBZNx8IQMzRFvy8oauLG_i1XIr6jgTs/edit?usp=sharing.",
